    content: `The word gospel comes from the Greek word euangelion and literally means a message of good news. No one becomes righteous before God by works of the Law. Everyone who dies without being justified will be separated from God forever. Jesus gave His own life to cover all sin forever. It is finished — Tetelestai — a past action with ongoing results. Eternal life is a present possession for those convinced Jesus will provide it. Faith is a persuasion of truth, incompatible with works. Whosoever believes in His Son enters the status of a child of God. The big three P's of Jesus: Person, Provision, Promise.`
